Name: ByControlPointsWeightsKnots
description: Create a BSplineCurve by from control vertices, weights, and knots. FROM ASM DOCS: Degree: Should be greater than 1 (piecewise-linear spline) and less than 26 (the maximum B-spline basis degree supported by ASM). Weights: All weight values (if supplied) should be strictly positive. Weights smaller than 1e-11 will be rejected and the function will fail. Knots: The knot vector should be a non-decreasing sequence. Interior knot multiplicity should be no larger than degree + 1 at the start/end knot and degree at an internal knot (this allows curves with G1 discontinuities to be represented). Note that non-clamped knot vectors are supported, but will be converted to clamped ones, with the corresponding changes applied to the control point/weight data. knot array: the array size must be num_control_points + degree + 1

Name: Height

In other words, if you create a Cuboid width (X-axis) length 10, and transform it to a CoordinateSystem with 2 times scaling in X, the width will still be 10. ASM does not allow you to extract the Vertices of a body in any predictable order, so it impossible to determine the dimensions after a transform.

Name: ByControlPointsWeightsKnots
description: Creates a NurbsSurface with specified control vertices, knots, weights, and U V degrees. There are several restrictions on the data which, if broken, will cause the function to fail and will throw an exception. Degree: Both u- and v- degree should be >= 1 (piecewise-linear spline) and less than 26 (the maximum B-spline basis degree supported by ASM). Weights: All weight values (if supplied) should be strictly positive. Weights smaller than 1e-11 will be rejected and the function will fail. Knots: Both knot vectors should be non-decreasing sequences. Interior knot multiplicity should be no larger than degree + 1 at the start/end knot and degree at an internal knot (this allows surfaces with G1 discontinuities to be represented). Note that non-clamped knot vectors are supported, but will be converted to clamped ones, with the corresponding changes applied to the control point/weight data.

Name: ByPointsTangents
description: Creates a NurbsSurface with specified interpolated points and U and V degrees. The resultant surface will pass through all of the points. The number of tangents must match the number of points in the corresponding direction. The resultant surface will be degree 3 in both the U and V direction.

Name: ByPointsTangentsKnotsDerivatives
description: Creates a NurbsSurface satisfying a collection of different surface characteristics. This is the most advanced surface fitting method. The resultant surface will pass through all of the points. The number of tangents must match the number of points in the corresponding direction. The resultant surface will be degree 3 in both the U and V direction. The corner derivatives should be second order (dP/dUdV) and should be supplied in this order [ lowU, lowV ], [ highU, lowV ], [ lowU, highV ], [ highU, highV ].

Name: Flatten
description: Flattens a nested list of lists by a certain amount.

Name: Insert
description: Inserts an element into a list at specified index.

Name: Reduce
description: Reduces a list into a new value by combining each element with an accumulated result.

Name: RemoveIfNot
description: Removes the members of the list which are not members of the specified type.

Name: RemoveItemAtIndex
description: Removes an item from the given list at the specified index.

Name: ReplaceByCondition
description: Replaces an object with a given substitute if the original object satisfies a given condition.

Name: ReplaceItemAtIndex
description: Replace an item from the given list that's located at the specified index.

Name: RestOfItems
description: Removes the first item from the given list.

Name: Scan
description: Reduces a list into a new value by combining each element with an accumulated result, produces a list of successive reduced values.

Name: Slice
description: Returns a single sub-list from the given list, based on starting index, ending index, and a step amount.

Name: Sublists
description: Build sublists from a list using DesignScript range syntax.

Name: TakeEveryNthItem
description: Fetches items from the given list at indices that are multiples of the given value, after the given offset.

Name: TakeItems
description: Fetches an amount of items from the start of the list.

Name: GroupByFunction
description: Use a function to determine how list items should be grouped.

Name: GroupByKey
description: Group items into sub-lists based on their like key values

Name: MaximumItemByKey
description: Returns the items from the list that generate the maximum values for the function supplied as the key projector

Name: MinimumItemByKey
description: Returns the items from the list that generate the minimum values for the function supplied as the key projector

Name: NormalizeDepth
description: Returns multidimensional list according the rank given.

Name: Reorder
description: Reorders the input list based on the given list of indices.

Name: Reverse
description: Creates a new list containing the items of the given list but in reverse order.

Name: ShiftIndices
description: Shifts indices in the list to the right by the given amount.

Name: Shuffle
description: Shuffles a list, randomizing the order of its items.

Name: Sort
description: Sorts a list by the items and return their indices.

Name: SortByFunction
description: Use a function to determine how list items should be sorted.

Name: SortByKey
description: Sort list based on its keys

Name: SortIndexByValue
description: Sorts a list by the items and return their indices.

Name: Transpose
description: Swaps rows and columns in a list of lists. If there are some rows that are shorter than others, null values are inserted as place holders in the resultant array such that it is always rectangular.

Name: Abs (number)
description: Finds the absolute value of a number.

Name: Abs (integer)
description: Finds the absolute value of a number.

Name: Acos
description: Finds the inverse cosine, the angle whose cosine is the given ratio.

Name: Asin
description: Finds the inverse sine, the angle whose sine is the given ratio.

Name: Atan
description: Finds the inverse tangent, the angle whose tangent is the given ratio.

Name: Atan2
description: Finds the inverse tangent of quotient of two numbers. Returns the angle whose tangent is the ratio: numerator/denominator.

Name: Average
description: Averages a list of numbers.

Name: Ceiling
description: Returns the first integer greater than the number

Name: Cos
description: Finds the cosine of an angle.

Name: Cosh
description: Finds the hyperbolic cosine of an angle (radians).

Name: DivRem
description: Finds the remainder of dividend/divisor.

Name: EvaluateFormula
description: Evaluates an NCalc formula with given parameter mappings.

Name: Exp
description: Returns the exponential of the number, the constant e raised to the value number.

Name: Factorial
description: Finds the factorial result of a positive integer.

Name: Floor
description: Returns the first integer smaller than the number.

Name: Formula
description: Evaluates mathematical formulas. Uses NCalc: http://ncalc.codeplex.com/

Name: Log (number, logBase)
description: Finds the logarithm of a number with the specified base.

Name: Log (number)
description: Finds the natural logarithm of a number in the range (0, ).

Name: Log10
description: Finds the base-10 logarithm of a number.

Name: Map
description: Maps the input value to a number between 0 and 1 based on the input range.

Name: MapTo
description: Maps the input value to a number between targetRangeMin and targetRangeMax.

Name: Max (int1, int2)
description: Returns the greater of two numbers.

Name: Max (value1, value2)
description: Returns the greater of two numbers.

Name: Min (value1, value2)
description: Returns the lesser of two numbers.

Name: Min (int1, int2)
description: Returns the lesser of two numbers.

Name: Pow
description: Raises a number to the specified power.

Name: Rand
description: Produce a random number in the range [0, 1).

Name: Random (seed)
description: Generates a random double in the range of [0, 1).

Name: Random (value1, value2)
description: Produce a random number in the range [lower_number, higher_number).

Name: RandomList
description: Produces a list containing the given amount of random doubles in the range of [0, 1).

Name: RemapRange
description: Adjusts the range of a list of numbers while preserving the distribution ratio.

Name: Round (number)
description: Rounds a number to the closest integral value. Note that this method returns a double-precision floating-point number instead of an integral type.

Name: Round (number, digits)
description: Rounds a number to a specified number of fractional digits.

Name: Sign (number)
description: Returns the sign of the number: -1, 0, or 1.

Name: Sign (integer)
description: Returns the sign of the number: -1, 0, or 1.

Name: Sin
description: Finds the sine of an angle.

Name: Sinh
description: Finds the hyperbolic sine of an angle (radians).

Name: Sqrt
description: Finds the positive square root of a number in the range [0, ).

Name: Sum
description: Find the sum of a series of numbers

Name: Tan
description: Finds the tangent of an angle.

Name: Tanh
description: Finds the hyperbolic tangent of an angle (radians).

Name: E
description: The mathematical constant e, 2.71828...

Name: GoldenRatio
description: The golden ratio, (1 + sqrt(5))/2 = 1.61803...

Name: PI
description: The mathematical constant Pi, 3.14159...

Name: PiTimes2
description: Pi Constant Multiplied by 2

Name: And
description: Boolean AND: Returns true only if both of the inputs are true. If either is false, returns false.

Name: Or
description: Boolean OR: Returns true if either of the inputs are true. If neither are true, returns false.

Name: Xor
description: Boolean XOR: Returns true if and only if exactly one of the inputs is true.

description: Convert between units of measure.

description: Converts an angle in degrees to an angle in radians.

Name: Number From Feet and Inches
description: Enter a length.

Name: RadiansToDegrees
description: Converts an angle in radians to an angle in degrees.

Name: Unit Types
description: Select a unit of measurement.

Name: If
description: Conditional statement

Name: LoopWhile
description: Constructs a while loop node given an initial value, a condition and a loop body.

Name: Pause
description: Pauses the current evaluation thread for a given amount of time.

Name: ScopeIf
description: Scoped If statement

Name: Code Block
description: Allows for DesignScript code to be authored directly

Name: Python Script
description: Runs an embedded IronPython script.

Name: Python Script From String
description: Runs a IronPython script from a string.

Name: Function Apply
description: Applies a function to arguments.

Name: Function Compose
description: Compose multiple functions.

Name: Concat
description: Concatenates multiple strings into a single string.

Name: Join
description: Concatenates multiple strings into a single string, inserting the given separator between each joined string.

Name: String from Array
description: Convert an array to a string representation.

Name: String from Object
description: Convert an object to a string representation.

Name: AllIndicesOf
description: No description available

Name: Contains
description: Determines if the given string contains the given substring.

Name: CountOccurrences
description: Counts the number of non-overlapping occurrences of a substring inside a given string.

Name: EndsWith
description: Determines if the given string ends with the given substring.

Name: IndexOf
description: Finds the zero-based index of the first occurrence of a sub-string inside a string. Returns -1 if no index could be found.

Name: LastIndexOf
description: Finds the zero-based index of the last occurrence of a sub-string inside a string. Returns -1 if no index could be found.

Name: Length
description: Returns the number of characters contained in the given string.

Name: StartsWith
description: Determines if the given string starts with the given substring.

Name: Center
description: Increases the width of a string by encasing the original characters with spaces on either side.

Name: ChangeCase
description: Converts the given string to all uppercase characters or all lowercase characters based on a boolean parameter.

Name: Insert
description: Inserts a string into another string at a given index.

Name: PadLeft
description: Right-aligns the characters in the given string by padding them with spaces on the left, for a specified total length.

Name: PadRight
description: Left-aligns the characters in the given string by padding them with spaces on the right, for a specified total length.

Name: Remove
description: Removes characters from a string.

Name: Replace
description: Replaces all occurrances of text in a string with other text.

Name: Split
description: Divides a single string into a list of strings, with divisions determined by the given separater strings.

Name: Substring
description: Retrieves a substring from the given string. The substring starts at the given character position and has the given length.

Name: ToLower
description: Converts the given string to all lowercase characters.

Name: ToNumber
description: Converts a string to an integer or a double.

Name: ToUpper
description: Converts the given string to all uppercase characters.

Name: TrimLeadingWhitespace
description: Removes all whitespace from the start of the given string.

Name: TrimTrailingWhitespace
description: Removes all whitespace from the end of the given string.

Name: TrimWhitespace
description: Removes all whitespace from the start and end of the given string.
